gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 139, Suns 122
gameRecap.excerpt: Jalen Brunson recorded a new career-high 50 points for the Knicks as they defeated the Suns, 139-122. Brunson went 9/9 on 3PM and added nine assists and a career high five steals for the Knicks, with Julius Randle adding 23 points, eight rebounds, and six assists in the victory. Kevin Durant tallied 29 points and six assists for the Suns in the losing effort. The Knicks improve to 14-10 in the regular season, while the Suns fall to 13-12.
